# Job Search HQ — Cursor Rules

Read `AGENT.md` before any job-related task. It contains all workflow logic.

## Who

[Your Name]. [Your City, Country]. [Relocation constraints].
Target: [salary range]. [Availability].
Roles: [your target role types].

## Workflows

- **Job intake:** Read AGENT.md § "Job Intake Workflow"
- **Job discovery:** Read AGENT.md § "Job Discovery"
- **Application prep:** Read AGENT.md § "Application Preparation Toolkit"

Before writing cover letters, read all docs in `profile/` — the more context, the more authentic the output.

Write in authentic voice — direct, specific, no corporate fluff.

## Key Files

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `AGENT.md` | All workflow logic (intake, scoring, discovery, application prep) |
| `profile/target-roles.md` | Scoring rubric — company tiers, role types, location rules |
| `profile/README.md` | Professional identity and strengths |
| `tracking/applications.csv` | Application log (canonical, gitignored) |
| `cv/cv.yaml` | CV source of truth (RenderCV format) |
| `tools/` | Python scripts (discovery, scoring, CV generation) |

## MCP Setup

Configure in `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (or project `.mcp.json`):
- **jobspy** — multi-board job search
- **memory** (mcp-memory-service) — semantic memory across sessions
- See `.mcp.json.example` for config templates

## Scoring Quick Reference

- Remote-first: +1.5
- Builder signals: +1
- AI-native company: +1
- Dream tier companies: floor 8
- Your city / remote: neutral. Your country: -0.5. Outside country: cap 5.
- Full rubric in AGENT.md and profile/target-roles.md

## Python

- Use `.venv/bin/python` (project venv at root)
- Never install packages globally

## Safety

- NEVER delete or overwrite `tracking/applications.csv` without explicit confirmation
- NEVER modify `profile/target-roles.md` without approval
- Ask before any bulk or destructive operation
